This MIT license covers Cuvée's source code only. Bundled datasets under
`data/` follow their own upstream licenses — see `docs/DATA.md` for the
full attribution table.

Climate data shipped here was generated using Copernicus Climate Change
Service information (ERA5 reanalysis and ECMWF SEAS5 seasonal forecast)
under the Copernicus License. Required attribution:

    "Generated using Copernicus Climate Change Service information 2024.
     Neither the European Commission nor ECMWF is responsible for any
     use that may be made of the Copernicus information or data it
     contains."

2025 NASA POWER backfill rows are public domain (17 U.S.C. § 105).
1855 château classification names are public domain (1855 historical
work). Derived terroir columns + the vintage-quality scoring schema are
original work covered by this MIT license.

If you fork or redistribute, carry the Copernicus attribution forward
in any product surface that displays or makes use of the climate data.
